    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into chips, then add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until tender and starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/caribbean-spiced-basa-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-crushed-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>ground paprika</strong>, <strong>ground allspice</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a plate</p><p>Give everything a good mix up until fully combined \u2013 this is your<strong> Caribbean spiced seasoning</strong></p><p>Press your <strong>fish fillet[s] </strong>into the <strong>Caribbean spiced seasoning</strong> so that one side is fully coated</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/caribbean-spiced-basa-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-crushed-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Zest your<strong> lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/caribbean-spiced-basa-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-crushed-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> mayo </strong>with the juice of <strong>half</strong> the<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lime[s] </strong>and the<strong> lime zest</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>lime mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/caribbean-spiced-basa-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-crushed-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> blanched peas </strong>to a pot with a lid, cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>(just enough to cover them) and add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 1 min or until they're warmed through, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/caribbean-spiced-basa-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-crushed-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>drained peas</strong> to the pot with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>, the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, the juice of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Mash the peas with a masher until they come together nicely \u2013 these are your<strong> crushed peas</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid to keep warm</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/caribbean-spiced-basa-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-crushed-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> fish </strong>(spice-side down) and cook for 3-4 min or until crispy, then cook for 3-4 min further on the other side or until cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> Caribbean spiced fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/caribbean-spiced-basa-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-crushed-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Caribbean spiced fish</strong> with the <strong>sweet potato chips</strong>, <strong>crushed peas</strong> and<strong> lime mayo</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
